values:
&nbsp;Hmm.&nbsp; I need to reinvest in my time and start updating this more often.&nbsp; Well.&nbsp; Interesting news:&nbsp; I'm graduating on May 9th!&nbsp; My undergraduate degree is finally over, after 7 years.&nbsp; Maybe 8, I lost count.&nbsp;&nbsp;If anyone feels like coming, I'm thinking about asking my sisters to make Carne Asada for the party! :-D

But thats not the half of it!&nbsp; In July and early August I will be participating in a bioarchaeological field school on Carriacou, a tiny island just north of Grenada.&nbsp; We will be excavating pre-columbian skeletal remains and material culture and attempting to determine their origins (yay biodistance analysis).&nbsp;&nbsp;

Whew,&nbsp;5 weeks on a&nbsp;Caribbean island, whatever am I going to do?&nbsp; I'm thinking about getting SCUBA certified through Arizona State before I&nbsp;leave, apparently it's one of the cheaper&nbsp;way's to go.&nbsp; And yet, as a desert rat, the thought of being immersed in water scares the living crap out of me.&nbsp; Hell, just the thought of being on a tiny island scares the living crap out of me.&nbsp; Especially since it will be the beginning of hurricane season.

Over Spring Break I helped out with some surveying and mapping of a site called Perry Mesa in Northern Arizona.&nbsp; It pretty much confirmed that I have chosen the correct major.&nbsp; Mostly because the statistical analysis part using GPS data was WAY to much fun, but also, seeing where people lived right near my hometown, but over 1000 years ago was interesting.&nbsp; We were surveying for Agave knives.&nbsp; They used these knives to cut down an agave to its heart and then they roasted the heart in underground firing pits (which you can still see today!) to make it stable for long term storage.&nbsp; My mom has actually been to a reenactment of the roasting ceremony, and says it doesn't taste all that bad.&nbsp; Course, you can't beleive her, she spent an entire year as a vegeterian, and she likes lentils.&nbsp; bleh.&nbsp;&nbsp;

I have no more to say.&nbsp; Except.&nbsp; nah nevermind.
